VALLEY PEOPLE 
Blue Cross of California reorganized its various divisions into three main 
groups and announced the executives who will head the new units. 
The Woodland Hills-based health insurer said D. Mark Weinberg was named 
executive vice president of its individual, small group and government services 
division, and Ronald Williams was named executive vice president of its health 
services and products group. 
Blue Cross also said Marvin Rich joined the company as an executive vice 
president of its financial and information services group. Rich formerly was 
executive vice president of California Federal Bank. 
In addition, Blue Cross named Ann F. Monroe to the new post of senior vice 
president of human resources and administration, which is part of the financial 
and information services group. 
